# Divide and Conquer & Greedy Algorithms Implementation

This project implements various divide-and-conquer and greedy algorithms in Java.

Compilation Instructions:

1. Ensure you have Java Development Kit (JDK) installed on your system.
2. Open a terminal/command prompt and navigate to the project directory.
3. Compile all Java files using the command:
   javac *.java

Running the Application:

1. After compilation, run the main class using:
   java AlgorithmTester

2. Follow the on-screen prompts to select an algorithm and input data.

Dependencies:
This project has no external dependencies and uses only standard Java libraries.

File Structure:

- AlgorithmTester.java: Main class with user interface
- ClosestPair.java: Closest Pair of Points algorithm
- DijkstraShortestPath.java: Dijkstra's Shortest Path algorithm
- HuffmanCodes.java: Huffman Coding algorithm
- KruskalMST.java: Kruskal's Minimum Spanning Tree algorithm
- MergeSort.java: Merge Sort algorithm
- PrimMST.java: Prim's Minimum Spanning Tree algorithm
- Quickhull.java: Quickhull algorithm for Convex Hull
- QuickSort.java: Quick Sort algorithm
- StrassenMatrixMultiplication.java: Strassen's Matrix Multiplication algorithm
- TSPApprox.java: Traveling Salesman Problem (Approximate) algorithm

Note: Ensure all files are in the same directory before compiling and running.
